{
  "book": 18,
  "chapter": 21,
  "sections": [
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 1,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Then Job replied: "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 1,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 2,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "“Listen carefully to my words; let this be the consolation you give me. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 2,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "“Listen carefully to my words; let this be the consolation you give me."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 2,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 3,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Bear with me while I speak, and after I have spoken, mock on. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 3,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "Bear with me while I speak, and after I have spoken, mock on."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 3,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 4,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "“Is my complaint directed to a human being? Why should I not be impatient? "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 4,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "“Is my complaint directed to a human being? Why should I not be impatient?"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 4,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 5,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Look at me and be appalled; clap your hand over your mouth. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 5,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "Look at me and be appalled; clap your hand over your mouth."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 5,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 6,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "When I think about this, I am terrified; trembling seizes my body. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 6,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "When I think about this, I am terrified; trembling seizes my body."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 6,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 7,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Why do the wicked live on, growing old and increasing in power? "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 7,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "Why do the wicked live on, growing old and increasing in power?"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 7,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 8,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "They see their children established around them, their offspring before their eyes. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 8,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "They see their children established around them, their offspring before their eyes."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 8,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 9,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Their homes are safe and free from fear; the rod of God is not on them. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 9,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "Their homes are safe and free from fear; the rod of God is not on them."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 9,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 10,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Their bulls never fail to breed; their cows calve and do not miscarry. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 10,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "Their bulls never fail to breed; their cows calve and do not miscarry."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 10,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 11,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "They send forth their children as a flock; their little ones dance about. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 11,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "They send forth their children as a flock; their little ones dance about."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 11,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 12,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "They sing to the music of timbrel and lyre; they make merry to the sound of the pipe. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 12,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "They sing to the music of timbrel and lyre; they make merry to the sound of the pipe."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 12,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 13,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "They spend their years in prosperity and go down to the grave in peace. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 13,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "They spend their years in prosperity and go down to the grave in peace."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 13,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 14,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Yet they say to God, ‘Leave us alone! We have no desire to know your ways. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 14,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "Yet they say to God, ‘Leave us alone! We have no desire to know your ways."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 14,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 15,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Who is the Almighty, that we should serve him? What would we gain by praying to him?’ "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 15,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "Who is the Almighty, that we should serve him? What would we gain by praying to him?’"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 15,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 16,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "But their prosperity is not in their own hands, so I stand aloof from the plans of the wicked. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 16,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "But their prosperity is not in their own hands, so I stand aloof from the plans of the wicked."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 16,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 17,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "“Yet how often is the lamp of the wicked snuffed out? How often does calamity come upon them, the fate God allots in his anger? "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 17,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "“Yet how often is the lamp of the wicked snuffed out? How often does calamity come upon them, the fate God allots in his anger?"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 17,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "“Yet how often is the lamp of the wicked snuffed out? How often does calamity come upon them, the fate God allots in his anger?"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 17,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 18,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "How often are they like straw before the wind, like chaff swept away by a gale? "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 18,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "How often are they like straw before the wind, like chaff swept away by a gale?"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 18,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 19,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "It is said, ‘God stores up the punishment of the wicked for their children.’ Let him repay the wicked, so that they themselves will experience it! "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 19,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "It is said, ‘God stores up the punishment of the wicked for their children.’ Let him repay the wicked, so that they themselves will experience it!"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 19,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 20,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Let their own eyes see their destruction; let them drink the cup of the wrath of the Almighty. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 20,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "Let their own eyes see their destruction; let them drink the cup of the wrath of the Almighty."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 20,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 21,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "For what do they care about the families they leave behind when their allotted months come to an end? "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 21,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "For what do they care about the families they leave behind when their allotted months come to an end?"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 21,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 22,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "“Can anyone teach knowledge to God, since he judges even the highest? "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 22,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "“Can anyone teach knowledge to God, since he judges even the highest?"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 22,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 23,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "One person dies in full vigor, completely secure and at ease, "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 23,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "One person dies in full vigor, completely secure and at ease,"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 23,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 24,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "well nourished in body, bones rich with marrow. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 24,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "well nourished in body, bones rich with marrow."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 24,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 25,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Another dies in bitterness of soul, never having enjoyed anything good. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 25,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "Another dies in bitterness of soul, never having enjoyed anything good."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 25,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 26,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Side by side they lie in the dust, and worms cover them both. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 26,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "Side by side they lie in the dust, and worms cover them both."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 26,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 27,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "“I know full well what you are thinking, the schemes by which you would wrong me. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 27,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "“I know full well what you are thinking, the schemes by which you would wrong me."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 27,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 28,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "You say, ‘Where now is the house of the great, the tents where the wicked lived?’ "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 28,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "You say, ‘Where now is the house of the great, the tents where the wicked lived?’"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 28,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 29,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Have you never questioned those who travel? Have you paid no regard to their accounts— "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 29,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "Have you never questioned those who travel? Have you paid no regard to their accounts—"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 29,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 30,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "that the wicked are spared from the day of calamity, that they are delivered from the day of wrath? "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 30,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "that the wicked are spared from the day of calamity, that they are delivered from the day of wrath?"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 30,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 31,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Who denounces their conduct to their face? Who repays them for what they have done? "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 31,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "Who denounces their conduct to their face? Who repays them for what they have done?"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 31,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 32,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "They are carried to the grave, and watch is kept over their tombs. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 32,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "They are carried to the grave, and watch is kept over their tombs."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 32,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 33,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "The soil in the valley is sweet to them; everyone follows after them, and a countless throng goes before them. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 33,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "The soil in the valley is sweet to them; everyone follows after them, and a countless throng goes before them."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 33,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "The soil in the valley is sweet to them; everyone follows after them, and a countless throng goes before them."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 33,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 34,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "“So how can you console me with your nonsense? Nothing is left of your answers but falsehood!” "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 34,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "“So how can you console me with your nonsense? Nothing is left of your answers but falsehood!”"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}